# =============================================================================
# Project Rules — Cisco Guest Desk (`centralino`)
# =============================================================================
# This file defines conventions for AI-assisted development. It is read by
# AI coding assistants to understand project standards.
# =============================================================================

## General

- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode) for backend and frontend.
- **Package manager:** npm workspaces (`backend/`, `frontend/`).
- **Module system:** ESM (`"type": "module"` in package.json).
- **Node.js version:** 22 LTS (matches the Dockerfiles and CI).
- **Makefile:** Use `make` targets for common tasks (`make test`, `make typecheck-backend`, `make docker-scan`, etc.). Never use raw npx/npm commands when a Makefile target exists.
- **Commands:** `make test` runs all 391 unit tests, `make typecheck` checks both workspaces, `make install` installs deps.

## Code Style

- **TypeScript strict mode** — no `any`, no implicit returns.
- **Named exports** preferred over default exports.
- **Async/await** with try/catch on every async handler (no unhandled rejections).
- **No secrets hardcoded** — all secrets via env vars (Key Vault references in production).
- **Path aliases:** Use relative imports within workspaces.
- **Formatting:** Standard TypeScript conventions (2-space indent, semicolons).

## Testing

- **Backend tests:** Vitest, 221 tests across 14 files. Run: `make test-backend`.
- **Frontend tests:** Vitest + React Testing Library, 170 tests across 10 files. Run: `make test-frontend`.
- **E2E tests:** Playwright, 22 tests (17 SSO mock + 5 calendar). CI-only.
- **Coverage:** Aim for >80% on new code. Run `npx vitest run --coverage` per workspace.
- **Test conventions:**
  - Use `data-testid` attributes on components for selectors (never getByTitle with broad regex).
  - Mock external services (WLC, email, Graph API) with `vi.mock()`.
  - Test happy path + error path + edge cases.
  - Use `screen` queries from `@testing-library/react`.
  - `userEvent` for interactions (not `fireEvent`).

## Docker

- **Dockerfiles:** Multi-stage builds, non-root users (`app` for backend, `nginx` for frontend).
- **Base images:** `node:22-alpine` (backend), `nginx:1.28-alpine` (frontend).
- **apk upgrade:** Always include `RUN apk upgrade --no-cache` in runtime stages.
- **.dockerignore:** Keep exclusions up to date. Exclude `.git/`, `node_modules/`, `.github/`, `scripts/`, `.env*`, build artifacts.
- **No docker-compose / local runtime stack:** Per platform guidelines (§11) the repo ships no `docker compose` stack or emulators. Local dev uses `make dev`; container validation happens on the Development environment via the pipeline.
- **Healthchecks:** Backend: `/api/healthz` (liveness) + `/api/readyz` (readiness). Frontend: nginx health endpoints.

## CI/CD

- **7 workflows** in `.github/workflows/`:
  1. `ci.yml` — TypeCheck + Unit Tests (every push/PR)
  2. `docker-security.yml` — Trivy scan on Docker images (every push/PR)
  3. `e2e-sso.yml` — SSO E2E tests (frontend-only, mocked)
  4. `e2e-postgres.yml` — Full E2E with PostgreSQL container
  5. `deploy-azure.yml` — 5-stage deploy to Azure Container Apps
  6. `provision-infra.yml` — Azure infrastructure provisioning
  7. `e2e-reusable.yml` — Reusable E2E workflow (called by e2e-postgres.yml)
- **Dependabot:** Configured for weekly minor+patch updates only (no major auto-PRs) via `.github/dependabot.yml`.
- **CI must pass** before merging (typecheck + unit tests + Docker scan for CRITICAL/HIGH).

## Database

- **PostgreSQL 15+** — via Azure Database for PostgreSQL Flexible Server (production) or a local instance (dev). Production auth is Entra ID token-based (the DB login role equals the backend UAMI name); no password user is provisioned.
- **Migrations:** Auto-run on startup unless `SKIP_MIGRATIONS=true`.
- **SSL:** `DB_SSL_ENABLED` env var controls SSL (required in production with Azure; certificates are validated unless `DB_SSL_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=false`).
- **Graph API email:** `MAIL_GRAPH_ENABLED` controls Microsoft Graph integration. Falls back to SMTP if disabled.

## Security

- **Vulnerabilities:** All CRITICAL/HIGH must be addressed before deployment.
- **npm packages:** Regular updates via Dependabot (weekly). Major versions reviewed manually.
- **Docker images:** Trivy scan on every push (via `docker-security.yml`).
- **Secrets:** Never hardcoded. Key Vault references in production (`@Microsoft.KeyVault(...)`).
- **Runtime:** Non-root users in all containers.
- **Session:** Signed cookies via `SESSION_SECRET`, stored in PostgreSQL via `connect-pg-simple`.

## Documentation

- **README.md:** Keep badges, quick start guides, and configuration docs updated.
- **CHANGELOG.md:** Follow Keep a Changelog format. Document all significant changes.
- **Code comments:** Use JSDoc for exported functions. Inline comments for non-obvious logic.
- **Env vars:** Document all env vars in `.env.example` with defaults and descriptions.
